President Trump and President Moon Jae-in of South Korea had a phone conversation to discuss their response to North Korea's destabilizing behavior. They emphasized the cooperation between the United States, South Korea, and Japan in addressing the issue. Both leaders pledged to apply diplomatic and economic pressure on North Korea and to make necessary preparations to deter and defend against the growing threat. They also agreed to strengthen the alliance through defense cooperation and to enhance South Korea's defense capabilities. President Trump approved South Korea's planned purchases of American military equipment.